# TailwindCSS Best Practices

## Context

- Applies to all TypeScript, TSX, and CSS files
- Ensures consistent TailwindCSS usage and styling
- Maintains design system consistency

## Critical Rules

- Use utility-first classes for rapid styling and consistency
- Create custom themes and extend Tailwind configuration for branding
- Utilize responsive design classes to ensure mobile-friendliness
- Avoid excessive use of `!important` to maintain CSS specificity
- Leverage Tailwind's JIT mode for faster build times
- Use semantic class names and avoid arbitrary values
- Implement consistent spacing and typography scales
- Use CSS custom properties for theme values when needed

